Section 3 Tasks:

Find the derivatives of the following: \(f(x)=x^2\) at x=3 \(P(a)=2(3a+2)^4−5\) at a=1.2 \(g(t)=−4t/(t2+1)^3\) at t=0

# First name the expressions
fx <- expression(x ^ 2)

fx_prime <- deriv(fx, name = "x")
fx_prime
## expression({
##     .value <- x^2
##     .grad <- array(0, c(length(.value), 1L), list(NULL, c("x")))
##     .grad[, "x"] <- 2 * x
##     attr(.value, "gradient") <- .grad
##     .value
## })
Pa <- expression(2 * (3*a + 2) ^ 4 - 5)

Pa_prime <- deriv(Pa, name = "a")
Pa_prime
## expression({
##     .expr2 <- 3 * a + 2
##     .value <- 2 * .expr2^4 - 5
##     .grad <- array(0, c(length(.value), 1L), list(NULL, c("a")))
##     .grad[, "a"] <- 2 * (4 * (3 * .expr2^3))
##     attr(.value, "gradient") <- .grad
##     .value
## })
gt <- expression((-4*t)/(t^2 + 1)^3)

gt_prime <- deriv(gt, name = "t")
gt_prime

Section 4

Create a penguin scatterplot for bill length vs depth

ggplot(penguins, aes(bill_length_mm, bill_depth_mm)) + 
  geom_point(aes(color = species)) + 
  labs(x = "Bill Length (mm)", 
       y = "Bill Depth (mm)", 
       title = "Penguin Bill Depth as a Function of Bill Length")
